drupalNodeEvent.title: Fifth Plenum of CCP's 19th Central Committee

field_speakers.processed: Prof. Manoranjan Mohanty (Honorary fellow ICS), Ambassador Kishan S Rana (Professor Emiretus, Diplo Foundation), Dr. Hemant Adlakha (Associate Professor, Jawaharlal Nehru University), Dr. Ritu Agarwal (Associate Professor, Jawaharlal Nehru University), Dr. T.G. Suresh (Associate Professor, Jawaharlal Nehru University), Dr. Bhim Subba (Assistant Professor, University of Hyderabad)

field_description.processed: Fifth Plenum of Communist Party of China’s 19th Central Committee held from 26 to 29 October 2020 was held in the backdrop of COVID-19 pandemic, changing geo-economic and political environment and the important quinquennial meeting on China's 14th Five Year Plan 2021-25. The workshop covers Internal & External Implications of the Plenum, Inclusive Development, 'Dual Circulation’ Economic Strategy and Personnel Movement and Ramifications
